{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeval\/toiso8601()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/TimeValProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/toIso8601()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"toIso8601","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"toIso8601()","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib15TimeValProtocolPAAE9toIso8601SSSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7TimeValC","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"platforms":[]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Converts ","type":"text"},{"code":"time","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into an RFC 3339 encoded string, relative to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This is one of the many formats"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"allowed by ISO 8601."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toIso8601"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ISO 8601 allows a large number of date\/time formats, with or without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"punctuation and optional elements. The format returned by this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is a complete date and time, with optional punctuation included, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"UTC time zone represented as “Z”, and the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tv_usec"},{"type":"text","text":" part included if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and only if it is nonzero, i.e. either","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ” or “YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.fffffZ”."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This corresponds to the Internet date\/time format defined by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and to either of the two most-precise formats defined by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the W3C Note","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Both of these documents are profiles of ISO 8601.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_format()"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_strdup_printf()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if a different","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variation of ISO 8601 format is required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time"},{"text":" represents a date which is too large to fit into a ","type":"text"},{"code":"struct tm","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. This is platform dependent. Note also that since"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeVal"},{"type":"text","text":" stores the number of seconds as a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"glong"},{"type":"text","text":", on 32-bit systems it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is subject to the year 2038 problem. Accordingly, since GLib 2.62, this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function has been deprecated. Equivalent functionality is available using:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["GDateTime *dt = g_date_time_new_from_unix_utc (time_val);","iso8601_string = g_date_time_format_iso8601 (dt);","g_date_time_unref (dt);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The return value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_val_to_iso8601()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been nullable since GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"2.54; before then, GLib would crash under the same conditions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"to_iso8601 is deprecated:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"#GTimeVal is not year-2038-safe. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"g_date_time_format_iso8601(dt) instead."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeVal/toIso8601()":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toIso8601"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timeval\/toiso8601()","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/toIso8601()","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"toIso8601()","abstract":[{"text":"Converts ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time"},{"type":"text","text":" into an RFC 3339 encoded string, relative to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This is one of the many formats","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allowed by ISO 8601."}],"deprecated":true},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeVal":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TimeVal","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"TimeVal","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timeval","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeVal"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Represents a precise time, with seconds and microseconds."}],"role":"symbol"},"http://www.w3.org/TR/NOTE-datetime-19980827":{"url":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Date and Time Formats"}],"title":"Date and Time Formats","identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","type":"link"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeVal/TimeValProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timeval\/timevalprotocol-implementations","abstract":[],"title":"TimeValProtocol Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/TimeValProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3339.txt":{"url":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RFC 3339"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt","title":"RFC 3339"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"}}}